# matplotlib.colors.to_rgba

matplotlib.colors.to_rgba(c, alpha=None)[source]

    
Convert c to an RGBA color.

Parameters

    
cMatplotlib color or `np.ma.masked`

alphafloat, optional

    
If alpha is given, force the alpha value of the returned RGBA tuple to alpha.

If None, the alpha value from c is used. If c does not have an alpha channel,
then alpha defaults to 1.

alpha is ignored for the color value `"none"` (case-insensitive), which always
maps to `(0, 0, 0, 0)`.

Returns

    
tuple

    
Tuple of floats `(r, g, b, a)`, where each channel (red, green, blue, alpha)
can assume values between 0 and 1.
